race.comment: Tricky. RAINBOW BLESSING (13) has her third race start and was beaten a whisker at Tamworth first-up. Presents fitter and races forward. She will get every chance to go one better. OCEAN CHILL (2) debuts for a top stable (Archibald) and placed here in a recent trial. Has a low gate and Collett's booking indicates they mean business. A bold run is on the cards. PARALIA (1) has been racing well without winning. Sits forward and has a key jockey switch to Bullock. Hard-fit and has to be considered. HE'S GOT GRUNT (6) is the Archibald's other runner and can show more over the longer sprint. Has the inside barrier and handy 2kg claim. Keep safe.
